    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nDescribe the problem (concisely).\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\nThis will focus on new tabpage\n```lua\nvim._with({ win = 0 }, vim.cmd.tabnew)\n```\n\nThis will stay in current tabpage\n```lua\nvim._with({ win = vim.api.nvim_get_current_win() }, vim.cmd.tabnew)\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\nNot sure which is correct, but `win=0`/`win=vim.api.nvim_get_current_win()` should have the same behavior\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.13.0-dev-214 g3cca237984-dirty` neovim/neovim@3cca237984\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.19.11-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-18T16:04:31Z",
